Titolo: BattleTech Centers

Anno: 1990

Descrizione: BattleTech Centers are commercial virtual entertainment venues that feature multiplayer virtual combat in the fictional BattleTech universe.  The games are played in fully enclosed cockpits with multiple screens, joysticks, and rudder pedals. The centers were initially created and operated by Tim Disney's Virtual World Entertainment, Inc.  Today, the gaming cockpits can now be found in various sites around the United States.

